      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SATISFIED (6) boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten one length (19.69) behind Magnificent Drop at this track. Top prospect. BALI CHARLIE (1) missed the frame on debut when fifth (31.25) at Q Parklands over 520m. Meets a moderate line up and should do much better. ASTON SAXON (8) was safely held on debut after settling well back when seventh (21.08) at Q Lakeside over 352m. Can do far better this time. WHIZZ BANG (2) is a Christopher Riordon-trained newcomer by Fernando Bale out of Bitter Delight. Drawn favourably and can capitalise. Profiles well so pay to keep very safe.",
